metadata.name: Ephemeral Fountain v1.0 #48
metadata.description:
This project originated with me thinking about how to do very realistic glass spheres that can be manipulated and moved within the THREE.js environment. Mixing that with several hundred ephemeral non-glass objects which are moving in a fountain-like flow, adding reflection and refraction to the glass, and combining it all in a physical existence which I playfully only impose on the non-glass objects nearby... in this world, glass can move through glass, with interesting effects similar to diamonds firing when light hits them at just the right angle! 

Extremely rare to get 8 glass spheres... By the randomness imposed, 30% will have one sphere, 30% two, 20% three, 10% four, 5% five, 3% six, 1% seven and 1% eight. Happy hunting!

metadata.name: Tema #59
metadata.description:
Tema is the second in a set of collections based on a month-long study of Edward Zajec, one of the early pioneers of generative art in the 1970s.

After gaining some traction with his original collection RAM, Zajec and his collaborating programmer Matjaz Hmeljak undertook a more complex algorithm titled "The Cube: Theme and Variation" (or TVC). The program laid out 8 unique elements in a grid, creating a three-dimensional viewing of objects in space. They published a paper about the underlying algorithm, found at: http://www.edwardzajec.com/tvc4/pil1/index.html

TVC was first printed in 1971, shortly after Zajec returned to Italy following his artistic studies in the US. It was programmed on an IBM 9044 & printed with a CalComp 563 plotter.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save a high-resolution version of the image

Made in p5js
Created January 2023
By @christine_hall

If you find one of the Golden Crown , in addition to a Super Rare edition, there are also prize

The lucky winners of the Gold Crown will get 2 Morixels Dog NFT

The Ancient smileys is unique random Generated 256 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 10 (81 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 629,254,080 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of the most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.
